No. 14 seed Ferris State University
and third-seeded Union College advanced to the semifinals of the
national menâ€™s college ice hockey tournament.  Ferris State beat No. 8 seed Cornell 2-1 and Union defeated
13th-seeded Massachusetts-Lowell 4-2 yesterday in the second
round of the National Collegiate Athletic Association
tournament.  In the second day of the first round games, No. 5
Minnesota-Duluth beat No. 11 Maine 5-2; No. 4  North Dakota 
topped Western Michigan 3-1; No. 1  Boston College  eliminated
16th-seeded Air Force 2-0; and No. 6 Minnesota defeated eighth-
seeded Boston University 7-3.  Boston College plays Minnesota-Duluth and North Dakota
meets Minnesota today in the remainder of the second-round
games.  The semifinals will be held April 5 with the championship
game April 7 in Tampa,  Florida .  To contact the reporter on this story:
